# Kubernetes Architecture

Kubernetes follows a control plane architecture.

Cluster Components

Control Plane
- API Server
- etcd
- Scheduler
- Controller Manager

Worker Nodes
- Kubelet
- Kube-proxy
- Container Runtime

How Kubernetes Works

kubectl command → API Server → etcd → Scheduler → Worker Node → Kubelet → Container Runtime

Explanation

API Server
Acts as the central communication hub for all Kubernetes operations.

etcd
Stores cluster state and configuration.

Scheduler
Decides which node should run a pod based on available resources.

Controller Manager
Ensures the cluster state matches the desired state.

Kubelet
Ensures containers run correctly on worker nodes.
```

